The paper is primarily focused on improving relevance ranking in Web search, which falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category. The proposed method involves learning visual features from Web page snapshots, which suggests the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also mentions a visual perception model inspired by human visual search behaviors, which falls under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of inverted indexing for efficient feature acquisition, which suggests the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for feature extraction, which falls under the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) category.
